last_episode_to_air.overview: After an event rattles the state of Montana, nothing will ever be the same.

name: Yellowstone
overview: Follow the violent world of the Dutton family, who controls the largest contiguous ranch in the United States. Led by their patriarch John Dutton, the family defends their property against constant attack by land developers, an Indian reservation, and Americaâ€™s first National Park.

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview: Amid shifting alliances and a growing list of enemies, the Dutton family's legacy is jeopardized like never before, and retribution is certain.

seasons.name: Season 3
seasons.overview: Jamie's loyalty is put to the test, Beth prepares to put up a fight, and the Dutton family forms new alliances.

tagline: Generations of blood have led to this.

episodes.name: Daybreak
episodes.overview: The Dutton family, owners of the largest ranch in Montana, fight ruthlessly to keep their land from the neighboring Indian reservation and the new chief seeking to reclaim it.

episodes.name: Kill the Messenger
episodes.overview: As the dust settles from the shootout, the Duttons deal with the potential repercussions. John calls in a favor and collects on some old debts. Jamie meets with the governor to do damage control.

episodes.name: No Good Horses
episodes.overview: The Duttons deal with a painful family anniversary. Kayce saves a young girl from danger. Jamie and Beth plan their respective political careers. Rainwater makes an ominous threat to the Dutton legacy.

episodes.name: The Long Black Train
episodes.overview: A secret about John comes to the surface. Beth shows Jenkins a rough night out. Quality time with Tate leads to a close call.

episodes.name: Coming Home
episodes.overview: As Kayce feels the heat from tribal police, Jamie works some legal magic. Rip recruits a new cowboy for the ranch, and a beaten-down Jimmy begins to find some respect. John makes a play to keep Kayce and Monica close to home.

episodes.name: The Remembering
episodes.overview: John reveals a family secret to Monica, Jamie ramps up his political career, Beth pushes John too far, Kayce and Rip butt heads, and a new partnership threatens Yellowstone.

episodes.name: A Monster Is Among Us
episodes.overview: Rip stumbles upon a dangerous and dire situation. A plan is set in motion designed to squeeze John Dutton and threaten his way of life. Monica begins a tough recovery.

episodes.name: The Unravelling (1)
episodes.overview: A Sheriffâ€™s investigation turns the heat up on Rip. Jamie makes a bold decision about his future and faces the consequences. With the walls closing in, John discovers which family and allies will stand with him and fight.

episodes.name: The Unravelling (2)
episodes.overview: John discovers his true alliances, Rip searches for answers, Jamie's political career is threatened, Beth takes on a new role, and Kayce returns home.

episodes.name: A Thundering
episodes.overview: Kayce settles into his new role at the ranch. A damaging article threatens to expose John. Rainwater pitches his new plan to the tribal council.

episodes.name: New Beginnings
episodes.overview: Kayce and Rip come to blows. Beth starts buying up land to protect the ranch. Monica begins a new chapter at the university.

episodes.name: The Reek of Desperation
episodes.overview: Rainwater teams up with Jenkins for a big business deal, but powerful new enemies look to block their plans. John and Beth groom a new political candidate.

episodes.name: Only Devils Left
episodes.overview: The Duttons try to figure out who's sabotaging their ranch, and Thomas Rainwater breaks ground on his casino, putting all the ranchers' businesses in jeopardy.

episodes.name: Touching Your Enemy
episodes.overview: Jamie tries desperately to walk back a previous mistake. Kayce tracks down evidence. Monica and Martin attend a traditional Indian horse relay.

episodes.name: Blood the Boy
episodes.overview: Jamie makes a drastic move in order to protect his family; Jimmy takes a shot at a rodeo competition; Walker tries to leave the ranch; Kayce and John spend quality time with Tate.

episodes.name: Resurrection Day
episodes.overview: Jamie is driven to a dark place while grappling with the consequences of his actions, Malcolm threatens Beth, and Monica and Tate move to the ranch with Kayce.

episodes.name: Behind Us Only Grey
episodes.overview: John and Rip seek revenge; Monica ponders the consequences of her living situation; Jimmy clears old debts.

episodes.name: Enemies by Monday
episodes.overview: The Duttons gear up for a final fight with the Becks; Beth helps Monica out of an uncomfortable situation.

episodes.name: Sins of the Father
episodes.overview: The feud with the Becks comes to a head as the Duttons scramble to save one of their own.

2.name: Season 2
2.overview: Amid shifting alliances and a growing list of enemies, the Dutton family's legacy is jeopardized like never before, and retribution is certain.

episodes.name: You're the Indian Now
episodes.overview: In the wake of the Beck Brothers, John reshuffles the political decks. Beth finds a trespasser on the ranch and learns that he may have big ambitions for the surrounding land. John helps Tate deal with his nightmares.

episodes.name: Freight Trains and Monsters
episodes.overview: Jamie starts a new job. Beth comes to a realization about Market Equities and visits Roarke. Rip searches for another ranch hand. A livestock agent goes too far.

episodes.name: An Acceptable Surrender
episodes.overview: Jamie plays cover-up and damage control with Hendon. Governor Perry hears a $6 billion pitch for a development right on the Yellowstone, and later makes some political maneuvers. Jimmy competes in a rodeo competition.

episodes.name: Going Back to Cali
episodes.overview: Beth shares a personal secret with Rip. John and the boys deal with some hostile trespassers from out of state. Rainwater reaches out to a powerful woman to help secure the future of Broken Rock.

episodes.name: Cowboys and Dreamers
episodes.overview: The reason for Beth and Jamie's toxic relationship is revealed; Kayce bends the rules to help a family in need; and Rip and the boys get into a confrontation with two men from John's past.

episodes.name: All for Nothing
episodes.overview: Beth reveals a secret to her father. John confronts two cowboys about old feuds. A search gets underway on the reservation.

episodes.name: The Beating
episodes.overview: Jamie has a major revelation. Beth makes plans for her future. Jimmy meets a rodeo legend. Rip's patience is tested.

episodes.name: I Killed a Man Today
episodes.overview: John and Tate enjoy a little horsemanship. Jamie convinces Kayce that Market Equities' offer might be in the family's best interest. Willa Hays and Beth play tug-of-war with each other's companies' stock. Monica departs on a dangerous mission to bring justice to Native women. Beth unsuccessfully attempts to convince John to sell off part of the ranch. Wade Morrow sends a message to John by exacting revenge upon Colby and Teeter.

episodes.name: Meaner Than Evil
episodes.overview: Jamie confronts his past. Rip approaches Kayce about an old problem. The bunkhouse crew looks to defend two of its own.

episodes.name: The World Is Purple
episodes.overview: John sits down at the negotiating table with former friends and foes; as the battle for the future of the Yellowstone heats up, nothing will ever be the same.

3.name: Season 3
3.overview: Jamie's loyalty is put to the test, Beth prepares to put up a fight, and the Dutton family forms new alliances.

episodes.name: Half the Money
episodes.overview: The coordinated attack on the Duttons continues as everyone searches for answers on who is responsible, and Rip delivers on a promise.

episodes.name: Phantom Pain
episodes.overview: The Yellowstone recovers and begins planning revenge. Rainwater receives an offer from a newcomer. Rip gets a surprise.

episodes.name: All I See Is You
episodes.overview: John seeks revenge with help from some unexpected allies. Kayce solves a problem with an unconventional method. Beth gives Carter his options. Jimmy prepares for a change.

episodes.name: Winning or Learning
episodes.overview: Jamie receives some surprising news; Beth receives an offer; Jimmy settles in on the road; tensions boil over in the bunkhouse.

episodes.name: Under a Blanket of Red
episodes.overview: John and Kayce are forced to deal with some newcomers in town; Lloyd is in the doghouse with Rip, and finds purpose in teaching Carter; Jamie seeks information about his father.

episodes.name: I Want To Be Him
episodes.overview: Beth confronts her father's houseguest; Kayce and his family search for a new home; Jamie seeks answers from Garrett; Lloyd loses his cool.

episodes.name: Keep the Wolves Close
episodes.overview: John is put in an awkward position by Gov. Perry; Carter works to earn back Beth's trust; Jamie is in for a big surprise.

episodes.name: No Kindness for the Coward
episodes.overview: Tensions escalate with the protestors, but Beth has a plan. Jimmy and Emily get closer. Monica and Kayce share a special moment.

episodes.name: No Such Thing as Fair
episodes.overview: John and Beth squabble; Jimmy has an important decision to make; Kayce begins a new quest; Jamie realizes Garrett's past might affect his own future.

episodes.name: Grass on the Streets and Weeds on the Rooftops
episodes.overview: To the Duttons, family is everything. However, newfound truths threaten that bond. Jimmy comes home, and has important decisions to make. Beth takes family matters into her own hands.

episodes.name: One Hundred Years Is Nothing
episodes.overview: John is sworn in as governor of Montana, settles into the powers of his office and makes bold moves to protect the Yellowstone, and the bunkhouse and the Duttons enjoy the Governor's Ball.

episodes.name: The Sting of Wisdom
episodes.overview: John makes a passionate speech to the state of Montana, a formidable new opponent from Market Equities arrives on a private jet, and the cowboys on the Yellowstone deal with a new problem.

episodes.name: Tall Drink of Water
episodes.overview: Beth heads to Salt Lake City to take care of unfinished business, a trap's set for Jamie, Kayce makes an important decision for his family, and Thomas Rainwater deals with mounting pressure.

episodes.name: Horses in Heaven
episodes.overview: John makes swift changes at the Capitol, the venom between Jamie and Beth reaches a boiling point, Rip updates John on his solution to the wolves, and the Yellowstone cowboys brand calves.

episodes.name: Watch 'Em Ride Away
episodes.overview: John tells Clara to cancel his Capitol meetings so he can brand cattle with the Yellowstone cowboys, and Beth's disdain for a perceived rival reaches a boiling point.

episodes.name: Cigarettes, Whiskey, a Meadow and You
episodes.overview: The Yellowstone enjoys an almost-perfect day branding cattle, Montana gets an unexpected visitor, Sarah sinks her teeth into Jamie, and Thomas Rainwater deals with a challenger from within.

episodes.name: The Dream Is Not Me
episodes.overview: John deals with a herd problem, Senator Perry delivers news to Thomas Rainwater, Jamie and Sarah plan their next move, and Beth discusses a new business plan with the ranch in mind.

episodes.name: A Knife and No Coin
episodes.overview: Jamie goes through with his plan, John lends support to an unexpected friend, the Yellowstone cowboys embark on a journey, and a flashback reveals the source of Rip's loyalty.

episodes.name: Desire Is All You Need
episodes.overview: After an event rattles the state of Montana, nothing will ever be the same.
